# NWN:EE Module Project

## NWScript files (`src/scripts/**/*.nss`)

- Use the correct prefix: `inc_`, `db_`, `sys_`, `evt_`, `qst_`, `adm_`, `mod_on_`, `plc_`, `cre_`, `trg_`.
- Keep event scripts thin — dispatch to `sys_*` modules, never put business logic in `mod_on_*.nss`.
- All database calls go through `db_*` include files. No raw NWNX SQL in gameplay scripts.
- Separate pure logic (arithmetic, state checks) from engine calls so Python tests can mirror them.
- Never call `DelayCommand` or `AssignCommand` inside include files (`inc_*`).

## GFF JSON files (`src/areas/`, `src/blueprints/`, `src/dialogs/`)

These files are produced by `nasher unpack`. Do not hand-edit them — use the Aurora Toolset, save, then run `nasher unpack` to get reviewable diffs. Editing JSON directly risks mismatched GFF structure.

## TypeScript MCP server (`tools/mcp/nwn-mcp/**/*.ts`)

- Validate all file paths through `resolveWorkspacePath()` before use.
- Use `safeArgs()` for command argument construction — never concatenate user input into shell strings.
- Gate dangerous operations (`aurora.launch`, `nwnx.start_server`, install to NWN_HOME) with explicit boolean flags from config.
- Return structured JSON from every tool handler.

## Python tests (`tools/testing/script-tests/*.py`)

- Always call `nwn.reset_state()` in `setUp()`.
- Mirror NWScript pure functions exactly in Python — same logic, same parameter names.
- Use only the Python standard library; no third-party test dependencies.

## SQL migrations (`database/migrations/*.sql`)

- Name: `NNNN_description.sql` (sequential, zero-padded).
- Wrap in `BEGIN; ... COMMIT;`.
- Add NOT NULL constraints and CHECK constraints for important columns.
- Add indexes for foreign keys and common query patterns.
- Never edit a migration that has been applied to any shared environment.
